@Node StreamConversion "Exec-Handler - Stream name conversion"

  @{b}Stream name conversion@{ub}

  The following steps are performed during stream name conversion:

  1. All slashes are removed and replaced by blanks.

  2. All backslashes are converted to slashes. This is neccessary for
     the "embedded" console window stream name.

  3. All dots ('.'), which are not part of a quoted text, are substituted
     by an equation symbol ('='). AmigaDOS strips all equations that are
     not quoted. So, either use the dot or quote the whole stream
     specification, if you want to pass arguments to the keywords.

@EndNode

